journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.label: Eusuchia

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Eusuchia (Huxley 1875). Amended definition.

Last common ancestor of Hylaeochampsa vectiana, Crocodylus niloticus, Gavialis gangeticus, and Alligator mississippiensis	 and all of its descendents.

phylorefs.label: Crocodylia

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Crocodylia (Gmelin 1789). Amended definition.

Last common ancestor of Gavialis gangeticus, Alligator mississippiensis, and Crocodylus niloticus and all of its	 descendents.

phylorefs.label: Gavialoidea

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Gavialoidea (Case 1930).

Gavialis gangeticus and all crocodylians closer to it than to Alligator mississippiensis or Crocodylus niloticus.

phylorefs.label: Pristichampsinae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Pristichampsinae (Kuhn 1968)	. New definition.

Pristichampsus rollinati and all crocodylians closer to it than to Gavialis gangeticus, Alligator mississippiensis, or Crocodylus niloticus.

phylorefs.label: Brevirostres

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition: Last common ancestor of Alligator mississippiensis and Crocodylus niloticus and all of its descendents.
phylorefs.curatorComments: If Gavialis and Tomistoma are sister taxa, Brevirostres is a junior synonym of Crocodylia.

phylorefs.label: Alligatoroidea

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Alligatoroidea (Gray 1844). 

Alligator mississippiensis and all crocodylians closer to it than to Crocodylus niloticus or Gavialis gangeticus.

phylorefs.label: Diplocynodontinae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Diplocynodontinae (Brochu 1999).

Diplocynodon ratelii and all crocodylians closer to it than to Alligator mississippiensis.

phylorefs.label: Globidonta

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Globidonta (Brochu 1999).

Alligator mississippiensis and all crocodylians closer to it than to Diplocynodon ratelii.

phylorefs.label: Alligatoridae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Alligatoridae (Cuvier 1807).

Last common ancestor of Alligator mississippiensis and Caiman crocodilus and all of its descendents.

phylorefs.label: Alligatorinae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Alligatorinae (Kälin 1940).

Alligator mississippiensis and all crocodylians closer to it than to Caiman crocodilus.

phylorefs.label: Caimaninae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Caimaninae (Norell 1988).

Caiman crocodilus and all crocodylians closer to it than to Alligator mississippiensis.

phylorefs.label: Crocodyloidea

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Crocodyloidea (Fitzinger 1826).

Crocodylus niloticus and all crocodylians closer to it than to Alligator mississippiensis or Gavialis gangeticus.

phylorefs.label: Crocodylidae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Crocodylidae (Cuvier 1807). Definition dependent on phylogenetic context.

Last common ancestor of Crocodylus niloticus, Osteolaemus tetraspis, and Tomistoma schlegelii and all of its descendents.

phylorefs.label: Mekosuchinae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Mekosuchinae (Balouet & Buffetaut 1987). Definition adapted from Salisbury & Willis 1996.

Last common ancestor of Kambara murgonensis, Australosuchus clarkae, Pallimnarchus pollens, Baru darrowi, Trilophosuchus rackhami, Quinkana	 fortirostrum, and Mekosuchus inexpectatus and all of its descendents.

phylorefs.label: Tomistominae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Tomistominae (Kälin 1955). Definition dependent on phylogenetic context.

Tomistoma schlegelii and all crocodylians closer to it than to Crocodylus niloticus.

phylorefs.label: Crocodylinae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Crocodylinae (Cuvier 1807). Definition dependent on phylogenetic context.

Crocodylus niloticus and all crocodylians closer to it than to Tomistoma schlegelii.

phylorefs.label: Osteolaeminae

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Osteolaeminae tax. nov. New definition.

Osteolaemus tetraspis and all crocodylians closer to it than to Crocodylus niloticus.
phylorefs.curatorComments: Not illustrated in fig 1, but it's resolution is pretty unambiguous, so I'm going to assert that it should resolve to "Osteolaemus tetraspis"

phylorefs.label: Crocodylidae (alt)

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Crocodylidae (Cuvier 1807).

Last common ancestor of Crocodylus niloticus and Osteolaemus tetraspis and all of its descendents.

phylorefs.label: Crocodylinae (alt)

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Crocodylinae (Cuvier 1807). At present, this would be redundant with Crocodylus.

Crocodylus niloticus and all crocodylians closer to it than to Osteolaemus tetraspis.

phylorefs.label: Gavialidae (alt)

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Gavialidae (Adams 1854). In a morphological context, Gavialidae would be redundant with Gavialis gangeticus.

Last common ancestor of Gavialis gangeticus and Tomistoma schlegelii and all of its descendents.

phylorefs.label: Tomistominae (alt)

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Tomistominae (Kälin 1955).

Tomistoma schlegelii and all crocodylians closer to it than to Gavialis gangeticus.

phylorefs.label: Gavialinae (alt)

journal.name: Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences

phylorefs.cladeDefinition:
Gavialinae (Nopcsa 1923).

Gavialis gangeticus and all crocodylians closer to it than to Tomistoma schlegelii.
